## Predicting Target Customers using Classification

In this notebook, we  predict customers most likely to be positive responders to an Affinity Card loyalty program. High Affinity Card responders (target value = 1) are defined as those customers who when given a loyaly or affinity card hyper-respond i.e. they increae their purchasing higher than the Affinity Card program's offered discount percentage.  This notebook builds and applies classification decision tree models using the SH schema data. All processing occurs inside Oracle Autonomous Database.

High Affinity Card responders (target value = 1) are defined as those customers who when given a loyaly or affinity card hyper-respond i.e. they increae their purchasing higher than the Affinity Card program's offered discount percentage. paragraphs.title: Show distribution of AFFINITY_CARD responders
paragraphs.text:
%sql

-- In this data set, hyper-responders to the Affinity Card loyalty program are represented as 1's. In this example, we target customers of this type.
-- Click on the bar chart icon and expand settings. Drag AFFINITY_CARD to Keys, CUST_ID Values, with nothing in Groups. Click CUST_ID in Values and select count. 

SELECT CUST_ID, AFFINITY_CARD FROM SH.SUPPLEMENTARY_DEMOGRAPHICS;

paragraphs.title: Graph HOUSEHOLD_SIZE grouped by AFFINITY_CARD responders
paragraphs.text:
%sql

-- Create a Bar chart of HOUSEHOLD_SIZE (Keys), AFFINITY_CARD (Groups), NUM_CUSTOMERS (SUM) (Values)

SELECT COUNT(CUST_ID) AS NUM_CUSTOMERS, HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, AFFINITY_CARD 
FROM   SH.SUPPLEMENTARY_DEMOGRAPHICS 
GROUP BY HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, AFFINITY_CARD;

paragraphs.title: Create view DEMOGRAPHICS4_V with desired columns for analysis
paragraphs.text:
%script

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW DEMOGRAPHICS4_V 
  AS SELECT AFFINITY_CARD, BOOKKEEPING_APPLICATION,
            BULK_PACK_DISKETTES, CUST_ID, EDUCATION,
            FLAT_PANEL_MONITOR, HOME_THEATER_PACKAGE, 
            HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, OCCUPATION, OS_DOC_SET_KANJI,
            PRINTER_SUPPLIES, YRS_RESIDENCE, Y_BOX_GAMES
     FROM   SH.SUPPLEMENTARY_DEMOGRAPHICS;
